    "Week 10 on reflective learning and journaling connects directly to how your own field trains. Reflective practice is a long tradition in nursing and allied health precisely because turning a hard clinical day into something you have thought about, rather than just survived, is how raw experience becomes real skill and steadier confidence. Building a genuine reflective habit now means you will keep learning across a whole career of change, new protocols, new technology, new evidence, rather than plateauing after your first few years.",
